**Season thirteen** of the [reality competition](/wiki/Reality_competition
"Reality competition") series _[America's Got
Talent](/wiki/America%27s_Got_Talent "America's Got Talent")_ premiered on May
29, 2018, on [NBC](/wiki/NBC "NBC"). [Howie Mandel](/wiki/Howie_Mandel "Howie
Mandel"), [Mel B](/wiki/Mel_B "Mel B"), [Heidi Klum](/wiki/Heidi_Klum "Heidi
Klum") and [Simon Cowell](/wiki/Simon_Cowell "Simon Cowell") returned as
judges for their respective ninth, sixth, sixth, and third seasons. Meanwhile,
[Tyra Banks](/wiki/Tyra_Banks "Tyra Banks") returned for her second season as
host.[1]

The live shows return to the [Dolby Theatre](/wiki/Dolby_Theatre "Dolby
Theatre"), beginning August 14, 2018.[2] AGT is co-produced by FremantleMedia
North America and Syco Entertainment, Cowell's company.[3][4]

Dunkin Donuts again sponsors the series for a fourth consecutive season.

## Preliminary
auditions[[edit](/w/index.php?title=America%27s_Got_Talent_\(season_13\)&action=edit&section=1
"Edit section: Preliminary auditions")]

The season had preliminary open call auditions in
[Orlando](/wiki/Orlando,_Florida "Orlando, Florida"),
[Cincinnati](/wiki/Cincinnati "Cincinnati"),
[Savannah](/wiki/Savannah,_Georgia "Savannah, Georgia"),
[Milwaukee](/wiki/Milwaukee "Milwaukee"), [Houston](/wiki/Houston "Houston"),
[Las Vegas](/wiki/Las_Vegas "Las Vegas"), New York City,
[Nashville](/wiki/Nashville,_Tennessee "Nashville, Tennessee"), and [Los
Angeles](/wiki/Los_Angeles "Los Angeles").[5] As in years past, prospective
contestants could also submit online auditions.[6]

Judges' auditions were taped from March 6-23 at the [Pasadena Civic
Auditorium](/wiki/Pasadena_Civic_Auditorium "Pasadena Civic Auditorium") in
Los Angeles.[7]

### Golden
buzzer[[edit](/w/index.php?title=America%27s_Got_Talent_\(season_13\)&action=edit&section=2
"Edit section: Golden buzzer")]

The golden buzzer will return for its fifth consecutive season. Any act that
receives the golden buzzer during the judges' auditions will be sent directly
to the live shows and will not compete in the Judge Cuts round.[_[citation
needed](/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed "Wikipedia:Citation needed")_] In the
first episode, [Tyra Banks](/wiki/Tyra_Banks "Tyra Banks") was the first to
press the golden buzzer for acrobatic and dance group Zurcaroh.
